00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:54,400
But my walks don't
normally end with a weapon

275
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,720
pressed against my back.

276
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:57,200
Now, how about yours?

277
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:59,520
SIENA: You always
were a smartass.

278
00:14:59,520 --> 00:15:01,280
Don't move.

279
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:02,600
I'll ask you one more time.

280
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,720
What are you doing here?

281
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:04,520
I told you.

282
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:08,840
I like taking my
evening strolls, Siena.

283
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:09,640
SIENA: Yeah?

284
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:11,560
Since when do you
like things like that?

285
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:13,080
SHARNID: People do
change, you know.

286
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:18,480
Really?

287
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,600
Is that right?

288
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,400
They sure do.

289
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:34,640
Siena, listen.

290
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:36,080
I'm telling the truth.

291
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:38,480
I was out taking a walk and
came across this commotion

292
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:40,120
just by accident.

293
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:41,000
That's why I'm here.

294
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,560
I promise.

295
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:44,520
I'm assuming that's
why you're here too.

296
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:49,480
Of course it is.

297
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:50,280
You see?

298
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:51,760
Now that we know
neither one of us

299
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:54,360
caused that ruckus, I'm
gonna put my hands down, OK?

300
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:03,120
Well, I gotta go.

301
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:04,040
See you, Siena.

302
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:04,800
Sharnid, wait.

303
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:07,920
Why'd you run out on us?

304
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:09,320
You really don't know?

305
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:11,840
That's why I'm asking.

306
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:12,840
Sure about that?

307
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:13,640
Tell me.

308
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:19,920
I wanna know why.

309
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:22,920
The three of us all made
a solemn promise together.

310
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:24,000
Did you forget that?

311
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,000
No.

312
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:34,760
Of course not.

313
00:16:34,760 --> 00:16:35,760
How could I?

314
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:36,560
Then why?

315
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:38,280
I'm gonna uphold
the pact we made,

316
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:40,760
but I have to do it in
my own way, all right?

317
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:42,080
And you believe
that you can do

318
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:45,080
it so much better with the 17th
instead of with our platoon.

319
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:45,880
Is that it?

320
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:48,680
I really don't know, Siena.

321
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,640
It's just‐‐

322
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:51,640
It's just what?

323
00:16:51,640 --> 00:16:54,040
Well, it's just when you
start wanting everything,

324
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:57,680
you usually end up losing
everything in the process.

325
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:59,800
In other words,
don't end up like me.

326
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,000
Later.

327
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:18,440
[LAUGHING]

328
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:29,400
[EXPLOSION]

329
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:41,880
No.

330
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:42,880
Not another one.

331
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:02,280
NINA: Layfon.

332
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:03,120
Nina.

333
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:04,400
What are you doing here?

334
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:05,840
I'm the one who
should be asking that.

335
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:07,160
What the hell happened?

336
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:10,920
Um, well, you see, guess I
kind of got in a little fight.

337
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:27,760
[SNORING]

338
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:30,160
GORNEO: Hey.

339
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,320
Wake up.

340
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:33,240
Shante.

341
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:34,320
I swear.

342
00:18:34,320 --> 00:18:36,920
All you ever seem to
do is eat and sleep.

343
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:37,920
Come on Shante.

344
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,280
Ah, wait a minute.

345
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:44,280
I better get that report.

346
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:46,120
[CREAKING]

347
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:49,000
Who's there?

348
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:53,040
HAIA: Well.

349
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:56,400
I guess you passed that test.

350
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:58,160
Hold on.

351
00:18:58,160 --> 00:18:59,000
Please.

352
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,120
Make yourselves at home.

353
00:19:00,120 --> 00:19:01,200
I insist.

354
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:03,440
Gee, thanks, but this
happens to be my room.

355
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:04,800
Argh.

356
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:06,760
[HISSING]

357
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:08,600
Now, why don't you come
out of there, Myunfa.

358
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:09,991
MYUNFA: K.

359
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:21,320
[MUSIC PLAYING]

360
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:51,800
Your majesty.

361
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:54,880
We cannot thank you enough
for your generosity, and are

362
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:57,040
now forever in your debt.

363
00:19:57,040 --> 00:19:57,800
No.

364
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,160
Think nothing of it.

365
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:00,840
Are your wounds healed?

366
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:02,000
DIRK: Yes.

367
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,080
They are, your majesty.

368
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:06,240
I've made a full recovery
thanks to the care

369
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:08,280
that you kindly granted me.

370
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:09,800
Please It was nothing at all.

371
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,560
Just a minor medical expense.

372
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:13,000
And one that was
painfully little

373
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,360
compared to all the
efforts that you've

374
00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:16,080
expended for this city, Dirk.

375
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:18,520
I'm undeserving of
such words, my queen.

376
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:22,160
You've helped Glendan time
and again, both by your own hand

377
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:26,560
and by the countless Heaven's
Blades you've trained.

378
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:28,880
But your majesty, I
have also failed you.

379
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:30,120
You didn't.

380
00:20:30,120 --> 00:20:31,320
He did.

381
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:33,720
His fate was brought about
by his own immaturity

382
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:36,200
and a lack of awareness
regarding the world.

383
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:38,560
You are by no means responsible.

384
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:41,440
Hm.

385
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:44,680
And speaking of Layfon, how
is he faring these days, Leerin?

386
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:51,320
I do recall that both you
and he were fairly close.

387
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:53,200
The two of you have been
exchanging letters ever

388
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:54,640
since he left, haven't you?

389
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:55,480
Yes.

390
00:20:55,480 --> 00:20:57,320
Um, I mean, yes, your majesty.

391
00:20:57,320 --> 00:20:59,440
We have.

392
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:00,240
Well, then.

393
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:01,760
Where is he and how is he doing?

394
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:04,120
He's good, your majesty,
and currently in a city

395
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:05,280
called Zuellni.

396
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,840
The academic city.

397
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:08,560
He was never very
good in school,

398
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:10,240
so it's a miracle
that he even passed

399
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:12,040
the entrance examination.

400
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:14,040
Was it you who
taught him to study?

401
00:21:14,040 --> 00:21:15,240
Yes, ma'am.

402
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,320
QUEEN: Good for you.

403
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:18,280
So tell me, what
do his letters say?

404
00:21:18,280 --> 00:21:19,760
Are his studies difficult?

405
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:21,760
Well, he seems to be
doing OK, and he said

406
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:22,720
he's made some new friends.

407
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:34,920
Oh, I see.

408
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:37,680
And so that weighs heavily
upon your mind, does it?

409
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:38,480
Yes, ma'am.

410
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:43,360
Um, my queen.

411
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:44,160
DIRK: Hm?

412
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:47,680
What is it, Leerin?

413
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:51,320
Layfon.

414
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:54,280
[MUSIC PLAYING]

415
00:21:59,760 --> 00:22:00,760
Your majesty.

416
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:17,640
Can he never return?

417
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:20,640
[MUSIC PLAYING]

